      <description>&lt;p&gt;Campaigners say the church continues to hide abusers under a ‘cloak of secrecy’&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Survivors of sexual abuse by priests have expressed dismay that the Church of England is set to uphold the confidentiality of confession against the urging of the archbishop of York.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A C of E working party, originally commissioned in 2014, has decided against the abolition or qualification of the “seal of the confessional”. Unless C of E bishops decide differently when they consider the group’s report, confessions of criminal acts will not automatically be passed on to the police.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/may/08/c-of-e-abuse-survivors-dismayed-as-seal-of-confessional-upheld"&gt;Continue reading...&lt;/a&gt;</description>
