      <description>&lt;p&gt;Chicken pie may not win you many followers on Instagram, but it is the ultimate comfort food&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If there’s any dish guaranteed to soothe ruffled feathers and salve a broken heart, it’s chicken pie. It’s not flashy food – that pale, creamy sauce doesn’t look great on Instagram, and the flavours whisper, rather than shout, with sweet leeks and salty bacon flattering the delicate charms of the chicken beneath a buttery, pastry crust. It’s quietly soothing, beige food of the very best kind. Serve with steamed greens and mash.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Prep&lt;strong&gt; 35 min&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Chill &lt;strong&gt;40 min&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Cook &lt;strong&gt;1 hr 50 min&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Serves &lt;strong&gt;4-6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/may/08/chicken-pie-masterclass-recipe-felicity-cloake"&gt;Continue reading...&lt;/a&gt;</description>
